Diabetes - Glossary Entry - Genetics Home Reference     A service of the U.S. National Library of Medicine Home   Search   Conditions   Genes   Understand Genetics   Resources   Glossary   About   Help       Glossary Glossary Home Search Genetics Home Reference Help Me Understand Genetics Diabetes - Glossary Entry Synonym(s) diabetes mellitus unspecified diabetes mellitus Definition(s) A disease in which the body does not properly control the amount of sugar in the blood. As a result, the level of sugar in the blood is too high. This disease occurs when the body does not produce enough insulin or does not use it properly. Definition from:  National Cancer Institute dictionary Genetics Home Reference obtains definitions from several sources.   Last updated: December 19, 2003 Last processed: December 19, 2003 This is a page from Genetics Home Reference. Contact Us Lister Hill National Center for Biomedical Communications U.S. National Library of Medicine National Institutes of Health Department of Health & Human Services Selection Criteria for Web Links - Copyright - Privacy - Accessibility